    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Ancient guardians of the barrow-mounds, barrow-wardens were once honored dead — warriors and priests interred with purpose. Now twisted by the spreading Rot, they serve as sergeants of the undead host. Their rune-blades deal biting cold damage, and their deep barrow-call can summon lesser thralls from the earth. The Law of the Grave binds them to their buried duty until the runes are shattered.</p>",
